h3cDldp2.name: h3cDldp2

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

h3cDldp2.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cDldp2.description: Device Link Detection Protocol (DLDP) MIB. Device Link Detection Protocol is a private Layer 2 protocol, which can be used to detect and shut down unidirectional links (fiber or copper links) to avoid network problems.

h3cDldp2GlobalEnable.name: h3cDldp2GlobalEnable
h3cDldp2GlobalEnable.description: Enable(true) or disable(false) DLDP on the device.

h3cDldp2Interval.name: h3cDldp2Interval
h3cDldp2Interval.description: Indicates the advertisement packet sending interval.

h3cDldp2AuthMode.name: h3cDldp2AuthMode
h3cDldp2AuthMode.description: Indicates the authentication mode. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. none: not authenticated. simple: authenticated by a clear text password. md5: authenticated by MD5 digest.

h3cDldp2AuthPassword.name: h3cDldp2AuthPassword
h3cDldp2AuthPassword.description: Indicates the authentication password. Setting the password to a zero-length octet string means deleting the password. When read, it always returns a zero-length octet string.

h3cDldp2UniShutdown.name: h3cDldp2UniShutdown
h3cDldp2UniShutdown.description: Indicates the shutdown mode when a unidirectional link has been detected. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. auto: the port will be shutdown automatically. manual: the port must be shut down manually.

h3cDldp2PortConfigTable.name: h3cDldp2PortConfigTable
h3cDldp2PortConfigTable.description: This table contains all ports that support DLDP.

h3cDldp2PortConfigEntry.name: h3cDldp2PortConfigEntry
h3cDldp2PortConfigEntry.description: This entry describes a port that supports DLDP.

h3cDldp2PortEnable.name: h3cDldp2PortEnable
h3cDldp2PortEnable.description: Enable(true) or disable(false) DLDP on a port.

h3cDldp2PortStatusTable.name: h3cDldp2PortStatusTable
h3cDldp2PortStatusTable.description: This table contains all ports enabled with DLDP.

h3cDldp2PortStatusEntry.name: h3cDldp2PortStatusEntry
h3cDldp2PortStatusEntry.description: This entry describes a port enabled with DLDP.

h3cDldp2PortOperStatus.name: h3cDldp2PortOperStatus
h3cDldp2PortOperStatus.description: Indicates the DLDP operating status on the port. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. initial: DLDP is not globally enabled. inactive: physical status of the port is down. unidirectional: all neighbors of the port are in 'unconfirmed' status. bidirectional: more than one neighbor of the port is in 'confirmed' status.

h3cDldp2PortLinkStatus.name: h3cDldp2PortLinkStatus
h3cDldp2PortLinkStatus.description: Indicates the DLDP link status of the port. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. down: the DLDP link status of the port is down. up: the DLDP link status of the port is up. If the port operating status is not 'inactive', 'unidirectional', or 'bidirectional', it always returns 'unknown'.

h3cDldp2NeighborTable.name: h3cDldp2NeighborTable
h3cDldp2NeighborTable.description: This table contains all port's neighbors.

h3cDldp2NeighborEntry.name: h3cDldp2NeighborEntry
h3cDldp2NeighborEntry.description: This entry describes a port's neighbors.

h3cDldp2NeighborBridgeMac.name: h3cDldp2NeighborBridgeMac
h3cDldp2NeighborBridgeMac.description: Indicates the bridge MAC address of a neighbor.

h3cDldp2NeighborPortIndex.name: h3cDldp2NeighborPortIndex
h3cDldp2NeighborPortIndex.description: Indicates the port index of a neighbor.

h3cDldp2NeighborStatus.name: h3cDldp2NeighborStatus
h3cDldp2NeighborStatus.description: Indicates the status of a neighbor. unknown: cannot be determined for some reason. unconfirmed: unidirectional communication between the port and its neighbor. confirmed: bidirectional communication between the port and its neighbor.

h3cDldp2NeighborAgingTime.name: h3cDldp2NeighborAgingTime
h3cDldp2NeighborAgingTime.description: Indicates the aging time of a neighbor. If the neighbor status is not 'confirmed', it always returns 0.

h3cDldp2TrapUniLink.name: h3cDldp2TrapUniLink
h3cDldp2TrapUniLink.description: This trap is generated when DLDP detects a unidirectional link, ifIndex and ifDescr identify the port.

h3cDldp2TrapBidLink.name: h3cDldp2TrapBidLink
h3cDldp2TrapBidLink.description: This trap is generated when DLDP detects a bidirectional link, ifIndex and ifDescr identify the port.
